        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 6:14PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 613 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Howell, or 13 miles northwest of Tremonton. This storm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tremonton, Cache, Plymouth, Howell, Riverside, Peter, Garland,
Fielding, Portage, Washakie, Collinston, Bothwell, and Thatcher.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 15 between mile markers 381 and 400.
Interstate 84 between mile markers 21 and 40.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
